regional_flowfreq is a small library of matlab codes to perform a regional flow frequency analysis using a log-PearsonIII model. The codes are made to work with times series data (*.ts3) released by the Water Survey of Canada.

Real-time hydrometric data can be viewed at https://wateroffice.ec.gc.ca/
The HYDAT data base can be download at https://www.ec.gc.ca/rhc-wsc/default.asp?lang=En&n=9018B5EC-1

The analysis will be run by the script doFrequencyAnalysis.m.
Absolute input and output path need to be entered in the doFrequencyAnalysis.m script. 

